      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions reproduced within ±5% of target flow rate and rotational speed; fluid temperature controlled to 37 ± 1 °C.",
      "rationale": "FDA experimental dataset provides inlet flow rates and impeller speeds measured with calibrated ultrasonic flowmeter (±2%) and tachometer (±0.5%). Temperature maintained at 37 °C ± 0.8 °C. Boundary condition fidelity confirmed at Gradation 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) agrees with experimental measurements within ±15% across all 5 operating points, with uncertainty intervals overlapping for at least 4 of 5 points.",
      "rationale": "Predicted NIH values compared against FDA experimental measurements across 5 flow-speed combinations. Agreement within ±15% achieved at 4 of 5 operating points; the 4500 RPM 3 L/min condition shows an 18.4% deviation with non-overlapping uncertainty bounds. The assessment team notes this exceedance is attributed to secondary recirculation zones not fully captured by the k-omega SST turbulence model at off-design conditions, and considers the overall predictive performance adequate for worst-case identification. Gradation 1 achieved against a Gradation 2 requirement."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
