      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are the primary regulatory endpoints for CPB device assessment. Power-law hemolysis model integrates shear stress and exposure time along Lagrangian particle paths, directly linking CFD outputs to clinical hemolysis risk. Full Gradation 2 relevance confirmed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
